## Slide 4: Low-Level Design — Module Breakdown

**Title:** Component Design & Responsibilities

```
src/
├── controllers/          ← HTTP request/response handling only
│   ├── authController       register, login, logout, reset
│   ├── ownerController      profile, schedule, services
│   ├── customerController   browse, slots, reviews
│   └── bookingController    create, confirm, cancel, reject
│
├── services/             ← All business logic lives here
│   ├── authService          credential validation, bcrypt
│   ├── slotService          slot generation + lunch exclusion
│   ├── bookingService       hold mechanism, state machine
│   ├── ownerService         salon & schedule management
│   ├── reviewService        rating aggregation
│   └── notificationService  email/SMS abstraction layer
│
├── models/               ← Sequelize ORM definitions
│   └── User, Salon, Service, SalonService,
│       Slot, Booking, Review, Notification
│
├── middleware/           ← Cross-cutting concerns
│   ├── authMiddleware       session checks + role guards
│   ├── validationMiddleware joi/express-validator rules
│   └── errorHandler         centralised error responses
│
└── jobs/                 ← Scheduled automation
    ├── releaseAbandonedSlots.js
    ├── autoConfirmBookings.js
    └── scheduler.js
```

**Booking State Machine:**

```
  PENDING ──(customer confirms)──► CONFIRMED
     │                                 │
     │(owner rejects / timeout)        │(service done)
     ▼                                 ▼
  REJECTED                         COMPLETED
     │
     │(customer cancels)
     ▼
  CANCELLED
```

