## Slide 7: Deployment Architecture

**Title:** Deployment — From Dev to Production

### Environment Configuration (.env)

```env
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=saloon_booking
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=<strong-password>
SESSION_SECRET=<32-char-random-string>
```

### Local / Single-Server Deployment

```
Internet
   │
   ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Nginx (Reverse Proxy · Port 80/443)     │
│  SSL Termination · Static File Serving   │
└─────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                  │ proxy_pass :3000
┌─────────────────▼────────────────────────┐
│  Node.js App (PM2 Process Manager)       │
│  pm2 start server.js --name salon-app    │
│  pm2 startup · pm2 save                  │
└─────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                  │ Sequelize (localhost)
┌─────────────────▼────────────────────────┐
│  PostgreSQL 14+ (systemd service)        │
│  DB: saloon_booking                      │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Setup Commands (Linux Production)

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies & run DB setup
chmod +x scripts/setup-linux.sh && ./scripts/setup-linux.sh

# 2. Start with PM2
npm install -g pm2
pm2 start server.js --name salon-app
pm2 startup && pm2 save

# 3. Nginx virtual host
server {
  listen 80;
  server_name yourdomain.com;
  location / { proxy_pass http://localhost:3000; }
  location /public { root /var/www/salon-booking; }
}
```

### npm Operational Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `npm start` | Production server |
| `npm run dev` | Dev with nodemon auto-reload |
| `npm run db:migrate` | Apply all migrations |
| `npm run db:seed` | Load demo data |
| `npm run db:reset` | Full reset: undo → migrate → seed |

