## Slide 8: Tech Stack & Project Structure

**Title:** Technology Choices & Codebase Organisation

### Tech Stack Summary

| Layer | Technology | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| **Frontend** | HTML5, CSS3, jQuery 3.7, Vanilla JS | Zero-build, lightweight, browser-native |
| **Backend** | Node.js 18+, Express.js 4 | Async I/O, huge ecosystem, fast to develop |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL 14+ | ACID compliance, relational integrity |
| **ORM** | Sequelize 6 + Migrations | Schema versioning, safe deployments |
| **Session** | express-session + connect-session-sequelize | DB-backed sessions, no extra infra |
| **Scheduler** | node-cron | In-process cron, no external queue needed |
| **Auth** | bcryptjs | Industry-standard password hashing |
| **Process Mgr** | PM2 *(production)* | Auto-restart, clustering, log management |
| **Proxy** | Nginx *(production)* | SSL termination, static assets, load balance |

